Traffic

(1) From the Hefei Xinqiao International Airport to the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel

The distance between the Hefei Xinqiao International Airport and the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel is about 37.7 km.

Ø  Route 1：By taxi, it takes about 45 min, 84 CNY.

Ø  Route 2：Take the Airport Bus Line 4 directly to the Swan Lake Hotel, get off and walk about 362 meters, you will arrive at the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel, and it takes about 56 minutes, 25 CNY. The bus time is from 08:20 to 21:30.

 (2) From the Hefeinan Railway Station to the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel

The distance between the Hefeinan Railway Station and the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel is about 7.8 km.

Ø  Route 1：By taxi, it takes about 15 min, 18 CNY.

Ø  Route 2：Take Bus No. 156 directly from the North Square of Hefeinan Railway Station to the Bus Station of Anhui Daily, get off and walk about 190 meters, you will arrive at the Swan Lake Hotel, and it takes about 45 minutes, 2 CNY. The bus time is from 06:00 to 22:00.

(3) From the Hefei Railway Station to the Hefei Swan Lake Hotel

The distance between the Hefei Railway Station and the Swan Lake Hotel is about 16 km.

Ø  Route 1: By taxi, about 30 min, 32 CNY.

Ø  Route 2: Take Subway Line 3 from the Hefei Railway Station to the Hefei Civic Center Station, get off and walk about 880 meters, you will arrive at Hefei Swan Lake Hotel, and it takes about 47 minutes. The subway time is from 06:00 to 22:25.

Note: The time and fare given above are estimated.

Please note peak time may need more travel time.

Brief introduction to Hefei

Hefei (population 4.8 millions) is the economic, political, cultural, transportation and tourism centre of Anhui Province. It is an ancient city with a history of more than 2000 years. The city has a total area of 7, 029 square kilometers. Hefei is located at the shore of ChaoHu Lake, one of the five largest freshwater lakes in China, and was awarded “Best Case City in Urban Competitiveness” in 2010 and “Top 10 Happiest Cities In China” in 2011. It is a lovely and attractive place to visit. There are also many famous landmarks in Anhui Province, including Yellow Mountain, the most beautiful mountain in China, and Jiuhua Mountain, one of the four sacred mountains of Chinese Buddhism. There are many historical and cultural sites in Hefei, including Sanhe Ancient Town, Memorial Temple of Lord Bao, and Xiaoyaojin, the classic battleground in the Three Kingdoms period, etc. Moreover, the local opera (Huangmei opera) and culinary enjoyments shouldn’t be neglected. The average day time temperature of Hefei in October is 20 degrees Celsius; the average night time temperature is 16 degrees Celsius.

Hefei is the hometown of BaoZheng (包拯) (999–1062) , who is the famous honest and upright official in Chinese history. BaoZheng was a much-praised official who served during the reign of Emperor Renzong of the Northern Song Dynasty in ancient China. Culturally, BaoZheng today is respected as the symbol of justice in China. Throughout history, his largely fictionalized stories have appeared in a variety of different literary and dramatic genres, and have enjoyed sustained popularity.

The three Kingdoms period was a period in Chinese history, referring to the years between the foundation of the state of Wei in 220 and the conquest of the state Wu by the Jin Dynasty in 280. The Three Kingdoms period was one of the bloodiest in Chinese history. The three kingdoms were Wei (魏),Shu (蜀), and Wu (吴). Xiaoyaojin in Hefei is one classic battleground in the Three Kingdoms period.

Landmarks in Anhui Province

Yellow Mountain

Yellow Mountain, located in Anhui Province, is also known as Huangshan Mountain, Mount Huang or Mt. Huangshan. It is a famous UNESCO World Heritage Site as well as one of the most visited scenic destinations in China. Praised as the loveliest mountain in China, Yellow Mountain has attracted millions of travelers to enjoy its breathtaking Magical Wonders - Odd-shaped Pines, Spectacular Rocky Peaks, Sea of Clouds, Hot Spring and Winter Snow”. As the popular ancient Chinese saying goes, "Trips to China's five great mountains render trips to other mountains unnecessary, and a trip to Huangshan renders the trips to the five great mountains unnecessary", Yellow Mountain will never disappoint any of its guests. Whenever you come, you always find visual-feast landscapes to enjoy - awesome sunrise and sunset, fantastic sea of clouds and incredible rocky peaks, beautiful pine trees, pure snow…

Jiuhua Mountain

Mount Jiuhua (Jiuhua Mountain), dedicated to Ksitigarbha Bodhisattva, is one of the four most sacred Buddhist mountains and a popular pilgrimage destination in China. From foothills to mountaintop, there are many ancient Buddhist temples and relics charting tracks of Ksitigarbha Bodhisattva and some great Buddhist monks. No matter you are a Buddhist or a traveler fond of Buddhist culture, the Mount Jiuhua Buddhist cultural tour will take you to worship the incarnation of Ksitigarbha Bodhisattva, visit the Buddhist shrines with different highlights and history and deeply explore Buddhism history and culture on Mount Jiuhua.

Hongcun Ancient Village

Hongcun is the China you think of when you think of ancient China. Many of the buildings in Hongcun can date back to the Song Dynasty (A.D. 960 - 1279) and is regarded as the best example of typical Hui-style architecture. Called“the ancient village in Chinese paintings”, Hongcun is so quiet, peaceful and beautiful which was listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2000, together with Xidi.

After Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon was filmed in Hongcun, more and more people get to know this ancient village. Many travelers choose to visit this beautiful village before or after the Mt. Huangshan trip. The moment you arrive in Hongcun, you will enjoy the charming landscape stretching before your eyes: morning mists, gray tilts, white walls, stone bridges, water lily ponds and verdant hills in the background. It is the real Chinese painting unfolding before you. Exploring this ancient village, you are recommended to see the South Lake, Moon Pond, Chengzhi Hall, South Lake Academy, Deyi Hall, Shuren Hall, Chengde Hall, Jingxiu Hall and Bi Garden, etc.
